# Overview

## Getting started

Install and launching R packages

The code chunk below use p_load() of pacman package to check if tidyverse packages are installed in the computer.
If they are, then they will be launched into R.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
pacman::p_load(sf,tidyverse)
```
:::


### Importing data


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
Ex_data <- read_csv("data/data.csv")
```
:::
